# CloudBees CLI + TUI (`cb`)

A lightweight Python tool to manage CloudBees from your terminal.
Two modes: **CLI** (scriptable) and **TUI** (interactive ncurses interface).

## Requirements

- Python 3.11+
- `click`, `httpx`, `cryptography` (the only external dependencies)

## Install

```bash
pip install -e .
# or
make install
```

## Quick Start

```bash
# Login (interactive prompt)
cb login

# Or non-interactive
cb login --url https://cb.company.com --username admin --password secret

# List jobs
cb jobs list

# Run a job
cb jobs run my-pipeline-job

# Launch TUI
cb --ui
```

## CLI Reference

```
cb login                        # Login and save encrypted credentials
cb auth profiles                # List saved profiles
cb logout                       # Remove stored token

cb jobs list [-o json|table]    # List jobs
cb jobs get <name>              # Job details
cb jobs run <name>              # Trigger a build
cb jobs stop <name> <build#>    # Stop a build

cb pipeline list                # List pipelines
cb pipeline run <name>          # Run a pipeline

cb users list                   # List users
cb users get <user-id>          # User details

cb system health                # Server health
cb system version               # Server version
cb system cache-clear           # Clear API cache
```

## TUI Keyboard Shortcuts

| Key       | Action                         |
|-----------|-------------------------------|
| `q`       | Quit                           |
| `Tab`     | Cycle through screens          |
| `1-5`     | Jump to screen directly        |
| `↑ / ↓`   | Navigate list                  |
| `r`       | Run selected job/pipeline      |
| `d`       | Detail view                    |
| `F5`      | Force refresh (bypass cache)   |
| `C`       | Clear cache                    |
| `l`       | Login                          |
| `L`       | Logout                         |

## Environment Variables

| Variable      | Description                            |
|---------------|----------------------------------------|
| `CB_PROFILE`  | Active profile name                    |
| `CB_PASSWORD` | Master password (avoid interactive prompt) |
| `CB_DB_PATH`  | Custom database path (default: `~/.cb/cb.db`) |

## Security

- Credentials are **never stored in plain text**
- API tokens are encrypted with **Fernet (AES-128)** using a key derived via **PBKDF2HMAC-SHA256** from your master password
- The Fernet key exists **only in RAM** during a session

## Cache

API responses are cached in SQLite with configurable TTLs:

| Resource       | TTL   |
|----------------|-------|
| jobs.list      | 60s   |
| jobs.detail    | 30s   |
| pipelines      | 120s  |
| users          | 300s  |
| system.health  | 15s   |

Use `F5` in TUI or `cb system cache-clear` to force refresh.
